cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) problems such as sentence similarity, entailment, and discourse relations, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of composition functions for embedding sentences, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents new models that improve the state of the art in transferable sentence representation learning, which is a topic in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge base triples, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and statistical relational learning (cs.SI).
